question_text: A user reports that documents printed from a specific workstation show repeated faded text and duplicate images, while printouts from other systems are normal. Which two issues should the technician investigate? (Select two)
answer_options: Faulty cleaning blade on the drum
correct_answer: Faulty cleaning blade on the drum
explanation: Incorrect drivers can cause output formatting problems, while a faulty cleaning blade may cause ghosting and faded duplicate images.
